          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Synagogue Chambers</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Philad.</placeName>
                                        <date>Shebat 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5611</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>January 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Your Letter of <date>8<hi rend="sup">th</hi>
                                                  Nov</date> addressed to the<lb/> wardens of our
                                        congregation was received and sub=<lb/>mitted to the Parnass
                                        and Adjunta who compose the<lb/> Board of Managers, it
                                        should have met with<lb/> an earlier answer but for a
                                        pressure of business<lb/> engagements, and in Conformity
                                        with your request<lb/> I proceed to give you as nearly as
                                        possible the information<lb/> requested,—The office of Hazan
                                        is vacant, and the<lb/> congregation have agreed to go into
                                        an election for one<lb/> on the <date>13<hi rend="sup"
                                                  >th</hi> April</date>, The term of service was to
                                        have been<lb/> originally ten years but owing to particular
                                        &amp; peculiar cir<lb/>=cumstances not necessary to be here
                                        narrated I am<lb/> of the opinion that no new incumbent will
                                        be engaged<lb/> at the outset for more than Three years and
                                        that the<lb/> ten years term will be rescinded. The salary
                                        to a<lb/> single man will be $1300, to a married man
                                        seventeen<lb/> hundred Dollars ($1700) per annum. The Hazan
                                        will<lb/> be expected to say all the usual prayers of
                                                  <date>sabbath</date><lb/> eve, morning, afternoon
                                        &amp; conclusion service, and on<lb/> holy-days &amp;
                                        festivals with no other aid except in the<lb/> Haphtara
                                        &amp; on <date>Kippur day</date> , it is not by law any
                                        part<lb/> of his duty to deliver English discourses but as
                                        it has<lb/> been for many years the custom to do so, an
                                        occa<lb/>=sional address or moral lecture in English will
                                        be<lb/> expected. The Hazan is to perform all marriage
                                        and<lb/> funeral services in the congregation and to
                                        attend<lb/> the seven days mourning service, he will be
                                        per=<lb/>=mitted to keep school and indeed his ability to
                                        teach</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>the Hebrew will be a great desideratum, but the congregation<lb/>
                                        will not be expected to do more than they bargain for
                                        and<lb/> it will depend on the popularity and abilities of
                                        the<lb/> successful candidate to make more by “Matanots” or
                                        by<lb/> teaching our youth. (he is also entitled to all
                                        marriage<lb/> fees) You remark in your letter “Should
                                        you<lb/> “gentlemen decide upon judging of my capability
                                        personally<lb/> “I should in all likelihood bring with me
                                        such certificates<lb/> “as to meet with your entire
                                        confidence, in that case<lb/> “I should much like to receive
                                        a minute account of the<lb/> “duties attached to the
                                        Hazanship before I undertake so<lb/> “expensive a
                                        voyage”</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have already given you an outline<lb/> of the
                                        duties of the office but the Board can take no<lb/> action
                                        or give any advice as to whether you should come<lb/> out or
                                        not, they are acting in this instance simply as<lb/> the <hi
                                                  rend="underline">mouth piece</hi> of the
                                        Congregation in announcing the exis<lb/>=ting vacancy, the
                                        forthcoming election &amp; in corresponding<lb/> with
                                        parties interested, but the election is made by<lb/> the
                                        members of the congregation at a general meeting<lb/> and
                                        not by the Board, it would no doubt be very<lb/> agreeable
                                        to be able to see and hear the candidates &amp;<lb/> judge
                                        personally of their qualifications, but as no provision<lb/>
                                        has been made to pay the <sic>travelling</sic> expenses of
                                        such<lb/> as wished to come on trial it must be left to the<lb/>
                                        <sic>judgement</sic> or inclination of the parties
                                        themselves whether<lb/> to come or not, Under all
                                        circumstances however<lb/> it will be very important to have
                                        from the best<lb/> sources the most ample testimonials of
                                        capacity and<lb/> standing.  I am dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">yours Very Respy</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">A: Hart</persName>,
                                        Parnass K.K.M.S.</p>
                              <p>To <persName>Mr S. Morais</persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>10 Bevis Marks</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>London</placeName>
                              </p>
